## Authentication

### Two-Legged OAuth (Client Credentials)

For server-to-server integrations using client credentials:

```csharp
using {{namespace}};

var client = new Client(
    domain: "your-institution.blackboard.com",
    clientId: "your-client-id",
    clientSecret: "your-client-secret"
);
```

### Three-Legged OAuth (Authorization Code + PKCE)

For user-delegated access (e.g., acting on behalf of a student or instructor):

```csharp
using {{namespace}};

var auth = new OAuth2Client(
    "https://your-institution.blackboard.com",
    "your-client-id",
    "your-client-secret",
    "{{auth.twoLegged.tokenEndpoint}}"
);

// Step 1: Generate the authorization URL with PKCE
var result = auth.GetAuthorizationUrl(
    "https://your-app.com/callback",
    scope: "read",
    state: "csrf-tok"
);
// Redirect the user to result.Url
// Store result.CodeVerifier

// Step 2: After the user authorizes, exchange the code
await auth.ExchangeCodeAsync(codeFromCallback, "https://your-app.com/callback", result.CodeVerifier);

// The auth client now holds the user's access token
var token = await auth.GetTokenAsync();
```

## Quick Start

```csharp
// List courses
var courses = await client.Courses.ListAsync();
Console.WriteLine(courses);

// Get a single course
var course = await client.Courses.GetAsync("externalId:INTRO-101");
Console.WriteLine(course.Name);
```

## Error Handling

```csharp
using {{namespace}};

try
{
    var course = await client.Courses.GetAsync("_invalid_id_");
}
catch (NotFoundError e)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Course not found");
}
catch (RateLimitError e)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Rate limited — retry after {e.RetryAfter}s");
}
catch (APIError e)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"API error {e.Status}: {e.Message}");
}
```

## Pagination

Paginated methods return `IAsyncEnumerable`:

```csharp
await foreach (var course in client.Courses.ListAllAsync())
{
    Console.WriteLine(course.Name);
}
```

